// OctopusExampleConfig — ScriptableObject template
//
// This file documents the expected structure. To set up:
//
// 1. In Unity, go to Assets > Create > Octopus Example Config
//    This creates Assets/Resources/OctopusExampleConfig.asset (git-ignored).
//
// 2. Fill in the fields in the Inspector:
//
//    Default Profile (used by most examples):
//      - apiKey:    your Octopus API key for OctopusAuth mode
//
//    Forced Login Profile:
//      - apiKey:    your Octopus API key for SSO mode
//      - authToken: a valid JWT token
//      - userId:    e.g. "user_01"
//      - nickname:  e.g. "UNITY USER"
//      - bio:       e.g. "Demo user for unity SDK"
//      - picture:   URL to a profile picture
//
//    Managed Fields Profile:
//      - apiKey:    your Octopus API key for SSO managed-fields mode
//      - authToken: a valid JWT token
//      - userId:    e.g. "user_01"
//
// 3. The asset is git-ignored and will not be committed.
